div.p:
-a @corresp attribute value can be used on more than one span in a given div the text XML, in which case it should only be
           defined by a single interp in that corresponding div in this file; the XSLT will pull the same interp into multiple notes in the same
           div in the output HTML;

-because the XSLT is written to pick up span elements in the text XML and number them in order, and then to find the 
              corresponding interp in this file by @corresp, the sequence of interp elements within a div in this file does NOT need to match
           the sequence of span elements in the text XML file;
